        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Essential Cyber security practices every business should follow in 2025"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "As cyber threats grow more sophisticated, businesses of all sizes must prioritise security to protect sensitive data and maintain customer trust. Whether you're a startup or an enterprise, these five cyber security best practices can help safeguard your digital assets in 2025."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph"
      },
      {
        "type": "image",
        "attrs": {
          "src": "https://raw.githubusercontent.com/bq-praveen-33/novel-data/main/docs/image/growtika-Jcw-i0fSqXg-unsplash.jpg-6ba4fb0c-25dc-4aca-a660-33837a4b7907",
          "alt": null,
          "title": null,
          "width": null,
          "height": null
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "1. "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ],
            "text": "Enforce Multi-Factor Authentication (MFA) Everywhere"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Passwords alone are no longer enough. MFA adds an extra layer of security by requiring a second form of verification (like a fingerprint or SMS code). Enable MFA for all employee accounts, especially those with admin access."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "2. "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ],
            "text": "Regularly Update and Patch Software"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Hackers often exploit vulnerabilities in outdated software. Ensure all operating systems, applications, and firmware are up to date with the latest security patches. Automated patch management tools can streamline this process."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "3. "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ],
            "text": "Train Employees on Phishing Awareness"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Over 90% of cyberattacks start with phishing emails. Conduct regular training sessions to help staff recognize suspicious links, fake invoices, and social engineering tactics. Simulated phishing tests can reinforce good habits."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "4. "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ],
            "text": "Adopt a Zero-Trust Security Model"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Instead of assuming internal networks are safe, Zero Trust verifies every user and device before granting access. Implement strict identity verification, least-privilege access, and micro-segmentation to limit breach risks."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "5. "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ],
            "text": "Back Up Data and Test Recovery Plans"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Ransomware attacks can cripple businesses in minutes. Maintain encrypted, offline backups of critical data and regularly test disaster recovery plans to ensure quick restoration after an attack."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ],
            "text": "Final Thoughts"
          },
          {
            "type": "hardBreak"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Cyber threats won’t disappear, but proactive measures can significantly reduce risks. By integrating these practices into your security strategy, you’ll be better prepared for the evolving threat landscape of 2025."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph"
      }
    ]
